This page explains the growth of the IT sector from 1999 to 2017 using a line chart. It shows how the growth percentage has changed over different years.

In 1999, the growth was low at around 5.88%. In 2000, the IT sector reached its highest growth of about 41%, which is clearly the peak in the chart.

After 2000, the growth dropped and stayed around 11% for a few years, showing a slower but stable growth. Later, around 2012 and 2014, the growth again went down to about 5.88%.

In 2017, the growth improved again and reached around 17.65%, showing that the IT sector started growing again.

Overall, this page shows that the IT industry had ups and downs, but it continued to grow over time in a steady way.
